biography.bio: Karin Baal was born on September 19, 1940 in Berlin-Wedding, Germany as Karin Blauermel. She is an actress, known for Lola, une femme allemande (1981), Le tunnel (2001) and What Have You Done to Solange? (1972). She has been married to Cevdet Celik since 2000. She was previously married to Volker Eckstein, Helmuth Lohner and Kalle Gaffkus.
biography.name: Karin Baal

biography.bio: Sylvia Lydi was born on July 16, 1933. She is an actress, known for Ein Mädchen von heute (1966), Bubusch (1962) and Hetzjagd (1970).
biography.name: Sylvia Lydi

biography.bio: Erna Haffner was born on September 24, 1912 in Berlin, Germany. She was an actress, known for Ein Mädchen von heute (1966), Chasse aux renards interdite (1966) and Ein ruhiges Heim (1970). She died in July 1989.
biography.name: Erna Haffner

biography.bio: Hartmut Reck was born on November 17, 1932 in Berlin, Germany. He was an actor, known for Section K3 (1988), Anfrage (1962) and Raskolnikoff (1959). He died on January 30, 2001 in Nienburg an der Weser, Germany.
biography.name: Hartmut Reck

biography.bio: Konrad Georg was born on December 25, 1914 in Mainz, Germany. He was an actor, known for Kommissar Freytag (1963), And Jimmy Went to the Rainbow's Foot (1971) and Mexikanische Revolution (1968). He died on September 8, 1987 in Hamburg, West Germany.
biography.name: Konrad Georg

biography.bio: Welbat was one of the founders of the cabaret "Die Stachelschweine". He was very famous in dubbing (German voice for Anthony Quinn, Peter Ustinov and the Cookie Monster). He was married to actress Sigrid Hackenberg.
biography.name: Alexander Welbat

biography.bio: Achim Strietzel was born on October 9, 1926 in Berlin, Germany. He was an actor, known for Der Andro-Jäger (1982), The Lost Honor of Katharina Blum (1975) and Der Herr Schmidt - Ein deutsches Spektakel mit Polizei und Musik (1971). He died on November 27, 1989 in Munich, Germany.
biography.name: Achim Strietzel

biography.bio: Rudolf Schündler was born on April 17, 1906 in Leipzig, Germany as Rudolf Ernst Paul Schündler. He was an actor and director, known for The Exorcist (1973), Suspiria (1977) and Le testament du docteur Mabuse (1933). He was married to Christine Laszar. He died on December 12, 1988 in Munich, Bavaria, West Germany.
biography.name: Rudolf Schündler

biography.bio: Gert Günther Hoffmann was born in Berlin-Lankwitz on February 21, 1929. After completing a commercial apprenticeship, he became interested in acting. He appeared in several stage plays before he started working as radio announcer for Berliner Rundfunk and as voice actor. One of his first voice works was dubbing Ben Johnson in Rio Grande (1950). Afterwards he spoke Rock Hudson, Paul Newman, Lex Barker, Michel Piccoli and Sean Connery in most of their movies. In some movies he was also the German voice of Clint Eastwood, Richard Harris, Kirk Douglas and Cary Grant. In addition to that he dubbed leading actors in many successful TV-Series, like William Shatner in Star Trek (1966), Patrick Macnee in The Avengers (1961) and Robert Culp in I Spy (1965). Hoffmann also worked as dialogue writer, dubbing director and talent scout (he discovered Thomas Danneberg in 1965). On screen he played minor as well as major roles and performed on stage in Berlin, Hamburg and Munich. In the 1970s he starred as Arnold Matofski in Sonderdezernat K1 (1972). One of the most well-known German dubbing voices, the "King of Dubbing", as he was often called, died of cancer on November 17, 1997 in Feldafing near Lake Starnberg, Bavaria.
biography.name: Gert Günther Hoffmann

biography.bio: Rolf Weih was born on February 8, 1906 in Barmen, Wuppertal, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. He was an actor, known for The 1,000 Eyes of Dr. Mabuse (1960), Amour bruyant (1940) and Erreur douloureuse (1940). He was married to Ira Kraut. He died on August 16, 1969 in Frankfurt am Main, Hesse, Germany.
biography.name: Rolf Weih

biography.placeOfBirth: Landsberg an der Warthe, Germany [now Gorzów Wielkopolski, Lubuskie, Poland]
biography.bio: Friedel Hensch was born on July 7, 1906 in Landsberg an der Warthe, Germany. She was an actress, known for Ein Mädchen von heute (1966), Ne fais pas le singe! (1961) and Ainsi sont les hommes (1957). She was married to Werner Cyprys. She died on December 31, 1990 in Hamburg, Germany.
biography.name: Friedel Hensch

biography.bio: Inge Brandenburg was born on February 18, 1929 in Leipzig, Germany. She was an actress, known for Erbe gesucht - Theater vorhanden (1970), Etwa im Oktober - Mehr oder weniger Heiteres und Herbstliches in Musik und Wort (1964) and Ein Mädchen von heute (1966). She died on February 23, 1999 in Munich, Bavaria, Germany.
biography.name: Inge Brandenburg

biography.bio: Monika Grimm is an actress, known for Modell Berta (1961), Mordnacht in Manhattan (1965) and Razzia au FBI (1966).
biography.name: Monika Grimm

biography.bio: Peter Müller was born on February 24, 1927 in Cologne, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. He was an actor, known for Ist ein Auto ein Auto? (1965), Ein Mädchen von heute (1966) and Das wird morgen vorbei sein (1961). He was married to Greta Thelen. He died on June 22, 1992 in Cologne.
biography.name: Peter Müller

biography.bio: Willy Hagara was born on June 4, 1927 in Vienna, Austria. He was an actor, known for Paprika (1959), Liebe, Mädchen und Soldaten (1958) and Der Haus-Tyrann (1959). He was married to Louise. He died on May 15, 2015 in Wiesbaden, Hesse, Germany.
biography.name: Willy Hagara
